cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the function computation problem in a communications network, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces the notion of entropic surjectivity and Little's law, which are related to data compression and processing, respectively, suggesting that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides insights into how to distribute computation depending on the entropic surjectivity of the computation task, which is related to machine learning and optimization, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as well.
